<br>
Essentially, every month, Mallo randoms (in the presence of witnesses) 1-X, X being the number of clerics on the list.  The lucky winner gets moved to the top of the list.<br>
<br>
The disadvantages: Those people near the top of the list will be slowed down, by a factor of 1/6.  Since approx 6 ragefires spawn per month, shuffling one person to the top of the list every month slows it down by 1/6.  However, the list still moves forward at a reasonable pace, AND newer members of the list have the chance (albeit small) to advance to the top via good fortune.  <br>
<br>
Thoughts? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=74028"target=new>Neuro the Strategist</a><BR>
Sorcerer of <a href="http://www.furys-edge.com"target=new>Fury's Edge</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/uflmutanteq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>flmutanteq</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/5/02 11:23:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.radzone.org/gnostik/luclinlook/gnostikbighead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Free For All on Ragefire 1-31 October ONLY</span><hr size=1> Morinkhan, my only fear with proposals like that is how cumbersome they might become (since we're talking about pops that now may or may not be highly competitive, all depending upon what the last few pops were -- a difficult &quot;decoding&quot; task.)<br>
<br>
But since we're talking about alternative approaches, how about the &quot;per guild&quot; approach instead of &quot;per cleric&quot;? Why not consider baking in some kind of pro-active reward for not-ganking (like &quot;the guild that helps the #1 cleric get off the list gets their clerics each bumped up one location&quot;)? Why not just toy with what happens after 3 hour mark (producing a &quot;rotation but snooze you lose&quot; style of rotation) coupled with minor revisions on how long you keep the #1 slot?<br>
<br>
I toss these out not because I'm advocate of any one of them, but they are ideas I have seen bandied about in the past in Ragefire threads that, IMHO, probably never really got shook out to see if a viable approach might be in there. I think any of those might provide something more workable than &quot;every 4th Ragefire is free-for-all.&quot;<br>
<br>
But I agree with your observation in general -- the list is dang near to that next generation of age, where it will start being a barrier to some guilds ever getting a cleric in-house. I'm not sure how well any of those guilds would &quot;compete&quot; in a FFA solution (so not sure if that solution scratches this itch) but finding a way to address that point seems worth the energy. <p>Faithfully yours,<BR><BR>


Pater <B>Gnostik Gnollhugger</B><BR>
<I>Faithful of Brell Serilis, High Priest of the Undercult</I><BR>
